## Annex I — essential cybersecurity requirements

| Req | Provided by openmv-ota | Customer must add | Status |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1(2)(a) No known exploitable vulns at market | Build-time SBOM + NVD/OSV scan | Act on findings | ☐ |
| 1(2)(c) Updates throughout support period | ROMFS OTA mechanism | Commit to a support period | ☐ |
| 1(2)(d) Protection against unauthorised access | ed25519 sig + anti-rollback + golden fallback | — | ☐ |
| 1(2)(e) Confidentiality of stored data | **Out of scope** (no image encryption) | Add encryption if applicable | ☐ |
| 1(2)(f) Integrity of stored data | Signature + SHA-256 + CRC32 (ROMFS) | Cover /flash, /sdcard | ☐ |
| 1(2)(h) Availability of essential functions | Trial-boot + golden image | — | ☐ |
| 1(2)(j) Mitigate impact of incidents | Auto-rollback to BACK | — | ☐ |
| 1(2)(k) Security event recording | `audit_log` pattern | Implement in app | ☐ |
| 1(2)(m) Vulnerability handling | OTA + SBOM + transparency log + disclosure | Run the process | ☐ |

